    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d25fn1">Sent to the White House Map Room as telegram No.
                            <gloss target="#t_Blue1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Blue</hi>
                        </gloss> 106; forwarded to the United States Naval Attaché, London, via Navy
                        channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>U.S.S. “<hi rend="smallcaps"
                                >Cummings</hi>”</placeName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d25fn2">Roosevelt
                            was en route from Auk Bay, Alaska, to Bremerton, Washington. See <hi
                                rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_10">p. 10</ref>, fn.
                            1.</note>] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-11">11 August
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 597 personal and top secret from the President for the <gloss
                        target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Your 750<note n="3" xml:id="d25fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_15">p. 15</ref>.</note> is
                    received at sea. I also deeply regret my inability to come to Scotland for this
                    meeting.</p>
                <p>It appears now that I should be able to arrive in Quebec on the 10th or 11th of
                    September for a meeting of the Combined Staff on the Teheran scale.</p>
                <p>My consultations with the military and naval commanders in the Pacific area have
                    been most interesting and valuable.<note n="4" xml:id="d25fn4">Concerning
                        Roosevelt’s conferences with MacArthur and Nimitz, July 27–28, 1944, see
                        Matloff, p. 482; Leahy, pp. 250–251.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
